<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 7 月 18 日星期二 06:14:03 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[The Man Charged With Steering the Yuan Through China’s Economic Turmoil]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>潘功胜有执行高风险任务的经验，但中国脆弱的经济引发新风险<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818268/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="潘功胜被给予了一定的空间来帮助制定人民币政策。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>潘功胜被给予了一定的空间来帮助制定人民币政策。安迪·黄/美联社<span>安迪·黄/美联社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059311"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059311"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/lingling-wei" itemprop="url" rel="author">魏玲玲</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/stella-yifan-xie" itemprop="url" rel="author">谢一帆</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jason-douglas" itemprop="url" rel="author">杰森·道格拉斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 18 日上午 12:02（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-charged-with-steering-the-yuan-through-chinas-economic-turmoil-37574af8"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>据知情官员透露，在中国国家主席习近平任命一位资深经济学家和银行家领导中国央行之前的几周内，一位资深经济学家和银行家一直在准备退休。</p><p>现在，潘功胜将接掌中国人民银行，因为它面临着紧迫的挑战：是否以及如何捍卫人民币。</p><p>由于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-barely-grows-as-recovery-fades-5652a92a?mod=hp_lead_pos1&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">世界第二大经济体陷入停滞</a>，人民币币值今年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yuan-under-pressure-as-u-s-china-rates-set-to-diverge-further-aa655bcd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">一直在下滑</a>。经济学家和一些北京官员担心，这种下滑可能会演变成一场溃败，从而破坏中国金融体系的稳定。</p><p>但经济学家表示，支撑人民币汇率也会带来风险，包括中国乃至世界其他地区的经济增长放缓。</p><p>据《华尔街日报》报道，习近平提拔潘这位 60 岁、在过去十年受过西方教育的中国人民银行副行长，是因为他被誉为一位经验丰富的技术官僚，能够<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-plans-to-appoint-a-new-central-bank-governor-56a878ea?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">与外国官员很好地合作</a>。</p><p>目前，习近平和他的新领导团队几乎没有透露北京方面的偏好，这给了新任中国人民银行行长一些帮助制定人民币政策的空间。</p><p>习近平挑选了一位曾处理过具有全球影响的高风险任务的潘先生。但多年来，潘作为政策制定者的身份一直在变化，这取决于最高领导层的优先事项。</p><p> 2012年习近平执政初期，潘基文将推动金融自由化作为领导人议程的一部分，以让市场力量对经济发挥更大的影响力。这有时会导致人民币更加自由，但也更加疲软。</p><p>其他时候，当人民币大幅贬值时，潘主张实施严厉的资本管制，以满足领导层保持人民币稳定的要求，尽管这会导致经济增长放缓。</p><p>布鲁金斯学会高级研究员、国际货币基金组织前中国区负责人埃斯瓦尔·普拉萨德表示：“潘基文将立即接受考验，以确定他作为致力于更加由市场决定汇率的改革者的资格。”</p><h3>人民币承压</h3><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="525" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818270?width=700&amp;height=525" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">今年人民币币值持续贬值，预计下行压力将持续。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Cfoto/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>过去六个月，人民币兑美元汇率已下跌逾6%。 6月下旬，一美元兑人民币一度达到7.2元左右，接近2008年全球金融危机以来的最低点。</p><p>最近几天，中国人民银行主要通过其为指导人民币日常交易而设定的官方汇率发出信号，表示其对快速贬值的容忍度<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-weakening-currency-is-becoming-a-headache-for-its-central-bank-372ec31d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">可能正在减弱</a>。人民币兑美元汇率已反弹至7.17。</p><p>然而，人民币的下行压力预计仍将持续。一个重要原因是，预计中国央行将<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-cuts-borrowing-rates-again-in-bid-to-juice-recovery-466b1d90?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">继续降息</a>以支持经济增长，而西方央行可能会进一步加息以对抗通胀。东西方的利率差距鼓励投资者将资金转移出中国，从而压低人民币汇率。</p><p>分析师表示，如果没有政府干预和中国经济增长强劲复苏，未来几个月美元的任何潜在疲软都不太可能改变人民币的下行轨迹。</p><p>美国外交关系委员会中国货币和债务专家布拉德·塞策表示，“如果中国央行不采取任何明显的阻力，人民币未来最有可能的走向是下行。”如果愿意的话，中国已经建立了庞大的战争基金来捍卫人民币，其中包括约3万亿美元的外汇储备。</p><p>权力与毛泽东相媲美的第三任中国领导人习近平明确表示，他对包括经济在内的所有重大决策拥有最终决定权。</p><p>但他仍在寻求政策建议，特别是针对货币管理等不稳定问题。预计他将与潘一起这样做，潘将被任命为中国人民银行行长，同时担任该行党内最高官员。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为今年中国经济会企稳吗？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>据知情人士透露，美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦在本月初<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/janet-yellen-says-u-s-china-making-progress-on-managing-economic-tensions-1e2c07?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">访问北京期间</a>会见了潘基文，并与他讨论了中国的货币管理问题。财政部官员一直在寻求更多有关北京如何管理其货币的信息，该部门长期以来一直批评中国在货币政策方面没有更加透明。</p><p>北京现在面临的部分挑战是，中国经济的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-fading-recovery-reveals-deeper-economic-struggles-31f4097b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">状况比过去几年更糟糕</a>，限制了央行的回旋余地。</p><p>如果采取更加不干涉的做法，让市场引导人民币走低，这可能会通过促进出口来帮助中国经济。但这也可能带来货币贬值和资本外流的风险，从而威胁中国的稳定，并波及全球市场。</p><p>然而，为捍卫人民币而进行更积极的干预将会降低中国出口的竞争力。这也将使中国央行更难继续降息，从而损害中国乃至世界的增长。</p><p>一些分析人士预计，潘基文将采取更多干预措施，以在短期内减缓人民币贬值。这可能为他赢得领导层的一些政治资本，而领导层似乎痴迷于经济稳定。</p><p>这些分析人士表示，潘基文可以利用政治资本推动人民币更加市场化，正如他和他的前任之前所主张的那样。</p><h3>中国的“加州旅馆” </h3><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="423" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818279?width=700&amp;height=423" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">潘功胜前几年担任政策制定者的角色取决于最高领导层的优先事项。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Felix Wong/南华早报/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>潘在中国大学接受过经济学培训，于 20 世纪 90 年代末在剑桥大学进行博士后研究，并于 2011 年在哈佛大学担任几个月的研究员。</p><p> 2000 年代，他领导了中国两家最大的国有银行的重组工作并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748704545004575352690672090642?mc_cid=480b08d787&amp;mc_eid=057b96de38&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">在美国上市，</a>之后他的职业生涯开始腾飞。潘于2012年加入央行，担任副行长，推动人民币和整个金融业更加市场化。</p><p> 2016年，潘被任命为中国最高外汇监管机构（隶属于央行）后不久，他说服最高领导人对中国企业的海外投资实施<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-issuing-strict-controls-on-overseas-investment-1480071529?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">严格限制</a>，以打击资本外逃。中国的资金外流导致人民币贬值，迫使央行动用1万亿美元（即当时外汇储备的四分之一<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-crusade-to-prop-up-yuan-neglects-other-pressing-needs-1492107144?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">）来阻止人民币贬值</a>。</p><p>随之而来的是更多的监管障碍，以阻止资金流出中国，这基本上抵消了多年来为让中国人更容易投资海外、更吸引外国人在中国投资而做出的努力——包括潘所倡导的一些努力。</p><p>此后，一些外国投资者将中国称为“加州旅馆”，投资者可以在那里退房，但永远不会离开。尽管如此，潘因寻求外国投资者解释央行政策而受到外国投资者的赞扬。</p><p> 2016年底资本管制举措后不久，他出席了中国欧盟商会举办的一个论坛，他告诉听众，央行当时的首要目标是“维护中国外汇市场的稳定” 。</p><p> 2018年，随着人民币再次承压，他曾警告交易员不要做空人民币。</p><p>自 2017 年以来，潘一直担任党的 205 名中央委员会候补委员，但在最近一次党代表大会上，他没有被任命为正式委员，这表明他没有获得晋升。</p><p>但习近平转向潘担任中国人民银行职务，是因为他的技术官僚知识在国家经济高层得到了广泛支持，包括习近平的长期经济顾问刘鹤等人以及包括前中国人民银行行长周小川在内的央行资深人士现任省长易纲，知情官员表示。</p><p>纽约咨询公司 22V Research 的中国研究主管迈克尔·赫森 (Michael Hirson) 表示：“潘的升职是政策连续性和技术官僚专业知识的选择，在中国面临经济挑战和政治动态的背景下，这应该被认为是令人放心的。”前美国财政部官员。</p><p> — <em>Grace Zhu 对本文做出了贡献。</em></p><p>写信给 Lingling Wei（ <a href="mailto:Lingling.Wei@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Lingling.Wei@wsj.com）</a> 、Stella Yifan Xie（ <a href="mailto:stella.xie@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">stella.xie@wsj.com</a> ）和 Jason Douglas（ <a href="mailto:jason.douglas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Jason.douglas@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 04:02:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-charged-with-steering-the-yuan-through-chinas-economic-turmoil-37574af8</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-charged-with-steering-the-yuan-through-chinas-economic-turmoil-37574af8<author><![CDATA[Lingling WeiStella Yifan XieJason Douglas]]></author><category>中央银行业务</category><category>金融服务</category><category>货币政策</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>货币/货币市场</category><category>商品/金融市场新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>潘功胜</category><category>货币政策</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>钱</category><category>货币市场</category><category>商品</category><category>金融市场新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>中央银行</category><category>金融服务</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Best of Frenemies: Saudi Crown Prince Clashes With U.A.E. President]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>沙特领导人与他的前导师渐行渐远，因为他们正在争夺海湾地区的主导地位，而美国在该地区的实力已经减弱<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816249/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="左为沙特王储穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼，即 MBS。对了，阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬，简称 MBZ。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>左为沙特王储穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼，即 MBS。右为阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬，简称MBZ。沙特通讯社/阿联酋总统事务部<span>沙特通讯社/阿联酋总统事务部</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001049776"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001049776"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/summer-said" itemprop="url" rel="author">Summer Said</a></span> 、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dion-nissenbaum" itemprop="url" rel="author">Dion Nissenbaum</a></span> 、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/stephen-kalin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Stephen Kalin</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name">Saleh al-Batati</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 18 日上午 12:01 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/frenemies-saudi-crown-prince-mbs-clashes-uae-president-mbz-c500f9b1"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> 12 月，沙特王储穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼在利雅得召集当地记者举行罕见的非正式简报会，并传达了令人震惊的信息。他说，该国几十年来的盟友阿拉伯联合酋长国“在我们背后捅了一刀”。</p><p>据参加会议的人士透露，他告诉与会者：“他们会看看我能做些什么。”</p><p> 37 岁的穆罕默德和他曾经的导师、阿联酋总统谢赫·穆罕默德·本·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬之间<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-and-u-a-e-clash-over-oil-yemen-as-rift-grows-ff286ff9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">出现了裂痕</a>，这反映出中东和全球石油市场对地缘政治和经济实力的竞争。这两位王室成员花了近十年的时间爬上了阿拉伯世界的顶峰，现在却在谁在中东发号施令的问题上发生争执，而<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mideast-challenges-mount-for-u-s-as-china-and-russia-make-gains-d2162906?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美国在中东的作用正在减弱</a>。</p><p>美国官员表示，他们担心海湾地区的竞争可能会让建立一个统一的安全联盟来对抗伊朗、结束也门长达八年的战争以及扩大以色列与穆斯林国家的外交关系变得更加困难。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="893" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816124?width=1260&amp;height=893" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> MBS（左）曾将MBZ（右）视为导师，但两位领导人最近一直存在冲突。上图是 2018 年两人在阿布扎比。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：沙特王宫</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>拜登政府一位高级官员表示：“这是两个雄心勃勃的人，他们希望成为该地区的关键人物和首选人物。” “在某种程度上，他们仍然合作。现在，双方似乎都对对方处于同一地位感到不舒服。总而言之，他们互相争斗对我们没有任何帮助。”</p><p>知情人士称，两人关系密切后，沙特人被称为 MBS，62 岁的阿联酋总统被称为 MBZ，他们已经有六个多月没有说过话了，他们的私人纠纷已经公开化。 。</p><p>阿联酋和沙特阿拉伯在也门存在不同的利益，这破坏了结束该国冲突的努力，而阿联酋对沙特提高全球石油价格的压力感到沮丧，这在石油输出国组织中造成了新的裂痕。</p><p>两国也日益成为经济竞争对手。作为穆罕默德·萨勒曼结束沙特阿拉伯经济对石油依赖的计划的一部分，他正在推动公司将其地区总部从阿联酋迪拜迁往沙特首都利雅得，迪拜是一个更受西方人青睐的国际化城市。他还启动了建立技术中心、吸引更多游客和开发物流中心的计划，以<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/dubai-uae-saudi-arabia-oil-ukraine-qatar-aa72c59?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与阿联酋作为中东商业中心的地位</a>相抗衡。三月份，他宣布成立第二家<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-unveils-new-airline-amid-jet-talks-with-boeing-4433dbeb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">国家航空公司，与迪拜排名靠前的阿联酋航空展开竞争</a>。</p><p>在软实力领域，沙特于 2021 年收购了英格兰足球俱乐部纽卡斯尔并投资了全球超级巨星球员，恰逢阿布扎比统治家族一位显赫成员拥有的曼城赢得了英格兰和欧洲足球冠军。</p><p>据海湾官员称，阿联酋总统 MBZ 因沙特王室的失色而感到恼火，阿联酋官员认为沙特王室犯了一些严重的错误。</p><h3>与伊朗打交道</h3><p>在回应《华尔街日报》的另一份声明中，一名代表政府发言的阿联酋官员表示，有关关系紧张的说法“绝对是错误的，缺乏根据”，而一名沙特官员则称这种想法“根本不准确”。</p><p>这位沙特官员表示：“阿联酋是沙特阿拉伯的密切区域合作伙伴，我们的政策在一系列共同关心的问题上趋于一致。”这位官员表示，两国与其他海湾邻国在政治、安全和经济协调方面开展合作。</p><p>这位阿联酋官员表示，他们的“战略伙伴关系基于区域繁荣、安全和稳定的相同目标和愿景。”</p><p> 12 月，在也门政策和 OPEC 限制问题上的分歧加剧后，MBS 召开了记者会。知情人士称，沙特领导人表示，他已向阿联酋发送了一份要求清单。 MBS警告说，如果这个较小的海湾国家不遵守规定，沙特阿拉伯准备采取惩罚性措施，就像2017年对卡塔尔所做的那样，当时利雅得断绝了外交关系三年多，并策划了经济抵制，来自阿布扎比的帮助。</p><p>据那里的人士透露，他对记者说：“这将比我对卡塔尔所做的更糟糕。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="842" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816189?width=1260&amp;height=842" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼一直在推动企业将总部迁至沙特首都利雅得（上图）。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：穆罕默德·本曼苏尔/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>自 12 月会议以来，MBS 采取了一系列<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-crown-prince-test-drives-nonaligned-foreign-policy-450ddefb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">外交行动，结束了因沙特突击队 2018 年杀害记者贾迈勒·卡舒吉而引发的政治孤立</a>。</p><p>他向中国寻求帮助，以恢复沙特阿拉伯与伊朗的关系，然后<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/syria-readmitted-to-arab-league-ending-over-a-decade-of-isolation-for-assad-6eb15d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">精心策划叙利亚重返阿拉伯联盟</a>，这一进程是阿联酋几年前启动的。 2011年，巴沙尔·阿萨德总统残酷镇压要求变革示威的叙利亚平民后，该国被驱逐出境。</p><p>穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼正在与美国就正式承认以色列事宜进行谈判， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-normalization-with-u-a-e-squeezes-saudi-arabia-11597397402?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阿联酋已于 2020 年承认了以色列</a>。穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼正在领导外交努力，以平息苏丹的暴力事件，阿联酋支持苏丹的敌对一方。</p><p>据两国官员称，为了缓和紧张局势，沙特阿拉伯和阿联酋交换了公报，概述了各自的抱怨和变革要求。</p><p>在对沙特投诉的尖锐回应中，MBZ 去年年底私下警告沙特统治者，他的行为正在破坏两国之间的关系。海湾官员表示，他指责沙特王储在石油政策上与俄罗斯走得太近，并在未与阿联酋协商的情况下采取冒险行动，例如与伊朗达成外交协议。</p><p>穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼缺席了呼吁中国领导人习近平访问利雅得的阿拉伯峰会，也没有参加阿拉伯联盟五月份允许叙利亚重返该组织的投票。一月份在阿联酋匆忙安排的区域峰会上，MBS 本人缺席了与阿拉伯领导人的会面。</p><p>国际危机组织中东和北非项目高级顾问迪娜·埃斯凡迪里 (Dina Esfandiary) 表示：“他们之间的紧张关系正在加剧，部分原因是穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼希望摆脱穆罕默德·本·扎勒曼的阴影。” “事情会变得更糟，因为两国的外交政策都变得更加自信和自信。”</p><h3>结成联盟</h3><p>沙特和阿联酋自称是最亲密的盟友，但早在 1971 年阿联酋脱离英国独立之前，两国关系就时常紧张。</p><p>阿联酋国父谢赫·扎耶德·阿勒纳哈扬对沙特对阿拉伯半岛的统治感到愤怒，时任沙特国王费萨尔多年来拒绝承认他的波斯湾邻国，寻求在各种领土争端中发挥影响力。 2009年，阿联酋放弃了在利雅得设立共同海湾中央银行的计划。时至今日，两国之间仍存在因石油资源丰富的土地而存在的领土争端。</p><p>随着MBZ和MBS的崛起，两国关系变得更加紧密。 2014 年，这位阿联酋王室成员在 54 岁时成为了该国事实上的统治者，当时他的同父异母兄弟、总统谢赫·哈利法·本·扎耶德因中风而衰弱。 2015 年，他的父亲萨勒曼国王登基后，MBS 开始积累权力，MBZ 开始培养这位当时年仅 29 岁的年轻沙特王子。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816128?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">阿布扎比统治家族一位显要成员拥有的足球队曼城队于五月庆祝了英超联赛的胜利。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：奥利·斯卡夫/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据《华尔街日报》报道，两人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-crown-prince-and-u-a-e-heir-forge-pivotal-ties-1502017202?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在广阔的沙特沙漠过夜露营</a>之前几乎不认识。据知情人士透露，在训练有素的猎鹰和一小群随行人员的陪同下，这次郊游——在海湾传统中大致相当于一轮总统高尔夫球——是他们友谊的转折点。</p><p> MBZ 和其他阿联酋高级官员在游说特朗普政府支持当时仍担任副王储的 MBS 方面发挥了关键作用。 MBZ 帮助策划了时任总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>2017 年的沙特阿拉伯之行，这为 MBS 提供了支持。这位沙特王子在下个月发动了一场宫廷政变，成为法定继承人，然后开始消除批评者和潜在的竞争对手。</p><p>在制定改革和开放其保守王国的计划时，MBS 向 MBZ 寻求指导，并聘请了阿联酋十年前用于类似计划的一些银行和顾问。</p><p>穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼和穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼组建了一个外交政策联盟，对也门进行干预，帮助阿卜杜勒·法塔赫·塞西在埃及政变中掌权，在分裂国家东部武装利比亚武装分子，并因与伊朗和伊斯兰主义者的关系而抵制卡塔尔。</p><p>此后，两人都试图让自己的国家摆脱这些干预。海湾官员表示，如今，穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼认为，阿联酋总统带领他陷入灾难性冲突，这符合阿联酋的利益，而不是沙特阿拉伯的利益。</p><p>已退休的中央情报局官员道格拉斯·伦敦 (Douglas London) 表示，MBS“不喜欢他，他想让他露面”。他现在是华盛顿智库中东研究所的非常驻学者。他表示，随着伊朗和恐怖组织的威胁消退，它们之间的紧张局势可能会升级。尽管如此，伦敦表示，沙特领导人已经制定了一种更实际的方法来领导他的国家，这使得他不太可能对阿联酋采取鲁莽行动</p><h3>欧佩克争端</h3><p>去年 10 月， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-u-a-e-scoop-up-russian-oil-products-at-steep-discounts-d327a2ee?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与俄罗斯结盟的</a>13 国石油生产组织 OPEC 决定大幅削减产量，此举令拜登政府措手不及，这一分歧浮出水面。阿联酋同意减产，但私下<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/before-opec-production-cut-saudis-heard-objections-from-a-top-ally-the-u-a-e-11667335415?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">告诉美国官员和媒体，沙特阿拉伯迫使其加入这一决定</a>。</p><p>这一动态反映出沙特和阿联酋之间在欧佩克政策上长期存在的争执，而利雅得长期以来一直主导着欧佩克组织，成为世界最大的原油出口国。阿联酋已将其石油生产能力提高到每天 400 万桶以上，并计划超过 500 万桶，但根据 OPEC 政策，石油产量不得超过约 300 万桶，这导致阿联酋损失了数千亿美元。收入。</p><p>阿联酋石油产能的增加也使其有可能上下调整产量，并随之调整全球油价。直到最近，只有沙特阿拉伯拥有这种市场力量。</p><p>据海湾和美国官员称，阿联酋的挫败感达到了极限，他们告诉美国官员，他们准备退出欧佩克。美国官员表示，他们认为这是阿联酋愤怒的表现，而不是真正的威胁。在 6 月份的 OPEC 上次会议上，阿联酋获准小幅提高其产量基准，而阿联酋能源部长则与沙特能源部长握手言和。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816199?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">四月，也门萨那，也门政府和胡塞叛军之间的囚犯交换后，人群做出反应。沙特阿拉伯和阿联酋在参与也门战争的过程中时而团结，时而冲突。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：yahya arhab/EPA/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>两位领导人之间的分歧有可能破坏结束也门战争的持续努力，这场战争使沙特、阿联酋和许多也门派系与伊朗支持的胡塞叛军展开对抗，胡塞叛军于 2014 年占领了该国大部分地区，包括首都，萨那。</p><p>阿联酋继续支持也门分裂主义运动，寻求在南部恢复也门国家。这可能会破坏保持国家团结的努力。多年来，沙特和阿联酋支持的武装分子共同努力击败胡塞武装，有时会互相用武器攻击对方。</p><p>去年12月，阿联酋与沙特支持的也门总统领导委员会签署了一项安全协议，赋予阿布扎比干预也门及其沿海水域的权利。沙特官员认为这是对其也门战略的挑战。</p><p>沙特阿拉伯计划修建一条从该国经也门哈德拉毛省通往阿拉伯海的管道，并在该地区首府穆卡拉设有一个海港。哈德拉毛特的阿联酋支持部队威胁到这些计划。</p><p>伦敦独立智库查塔姆研究所中东和北非项目的分析师警告说，敌对的也门军队正在为威胁正在进行的和平谈判的新冲突做准备。分析人士在一系列推特帖子中表示，“海湾地区的两个君主国正在该地区投射更多的权力，并采取更加激进的行为。” “也门只是第一条也是最活跃的前线。”</p><p>也门官员表示，如果沙特现在从也门撤军，胡塞武装控制的北部将与伊朗结盟，南部将与阿联酋结盟，使利雅得在战争中几乎没有什么可展示的，这反映了沙特的担忧。</p><h3>拜登的目标</h3><p>沙特与阿联酋的竞争让拜登政府感到烦恼，拜登政府希望利雅得和阿布扎比等友好的海湾国家首都帮助组建针对伊朗的统一战线。结束引发人道主义灾难的也门战争也是政府的一项重要外交政策目标，政府希望该地区和石油市场保持稳定。</p><p>在乌克兰和中国等重要问题上，MBS 和 MBZ 都<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-saudi-relations-biden-mbs-animosity-11666623661?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与华盛顿不完全一致</a>。美国官员越来越担心<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gulf-leader-tests-u-s-ties-with-moves-toward-russia-china-ecf9b779?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">MBZ与北京和莫斯科的接触</a>，MBS和MBS一样与他们建立了更牢固的关系。</p><p>拜登上任时承诺，由于卡舒吉被杀事件，将把沙特视为贱民国家，而穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼则表示，这并不是他下令的。相反， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-middle-east-trip-is-a-high-risk-bid-to-reset-saudi-relations-11657481150?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">拜登于 2022 年 7 月访问了沙特阿拉伯</a>，帮助结束了他的孤立状态。现在，一直犹豫是否与沙特接触的美国公司正在重新考虑。随着年底截止日期的临近，那些与沙特政府签订合同的公司在利雅得建立基地而不是从迪拜飞来，这种兴趣可能会加速。</p><p>知情人士称，拜登政府促成了穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼与阿联酋总统的弟弟谢赫·塔农·本·扎耶德的会面，谢赫·塔农·本·扎耶德曾被视为沙特王储的心腹。知情人士称，塔赫农已被排除在外，至少六次前往沙特，但在获得美国帮助之前都没有与穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼会面。</p><p>知情人士称，MBS告诉塔赫农，阿联酋不应扰乱也门的停火谈判，该谈判由沙特主导，并承诺向阿联酋做出让步。但后来他告诉顾问们，他们不应该改变对阿联酋的任何政策。知情人士说，他对顾问们说，“我不再信任他们了”。</p><p>写信给 Summer Said ( <a href="mailto:summer.said@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">summer.said@wsj.com</a> )、Dion Nissenbaum ( <a href="mailto:dion.nissenbaum@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dion.nissenbaum@wsj.com</a> ) 和 Stephen Kalin ( <a href="mailto:stephen.kalin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">stephen.kalin@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 04:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/frenmies-saudi-crown-prince-mbs-clashes-uae-president-mbz-c500f9b1</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/frenmies-saudi-crown-prince-mbs-clashes-uae-president-mbz-c500f9b1<author><![CDATA[Summer SaidDion NissenbaumStephen Kalin]]></author><category>领导者</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>王室成员</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>王室成员</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukraine Adopts Slow Approach to Counteroffensive]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>数辆坦克和步兵战车的迅速损失震惊了乌克兰及其西方支持者<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818058/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="尤里·乌尔辛（Yuriy Ulshyn），也被称为“希腊人”，带领他的战友们来到巴赫穆特附近由乌克兰军队控制的地区。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>尤里·乌尔辛（Yuriy Ulshyn），也被称为“希腊人”，带领他的战友们来到巴赫穆特附近由乌克兰军队控制的地区。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059643"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059643"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/james-marson" itemprop="url" rel="author">James Marson</a></span> / 摄影：Emanuele Satolli 为《华尔街日报》拍摄</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 18 日中午 12:00（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>乌克兰奥里克夫——在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-counteroffensive-frontlines-russia-add3e4e4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰反攻</a>六周后，阿纳托利·哈琴科上尉和他的侦察连本应在被西方提供的装甲车刺穿的俄罗斯防线后方数英里处造成严重破坏。</p><p>相反，在许多车辆陷入雷区后，哈琴科和他的手下正在训练如何有条不紊地步行前进，从一排树移动到另一排树，面临<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-counterattack-is-heavy-going-west-says-as-russian-resists-dc6fb4b4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">着一次一块地夺回自己国家的</a>前景。</p><p> “我们没有什么可失去的，”哈琴科说。 “胜利不仅重要，而且是唯一的选择，否则我们都会死。”</p><p>乌克兰于6月初发起反攻，旨在夺回<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/putin-condemns-western-support-for-ukraine-as-russias-battlefield-losses-mount-2c09554f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">被莫斯科占领的乌克兰近20%领土中的</a>部分领土。西方为这场战役提供了数十辆坦克和步兵战车，并训练了数千名乌克兰军队。</p><p>数辆坦克和步兵战车的迅速损失，其中许多被地雷或攻击直升机发射的导弹打动，令乌克兰及其西方支持者感到震惊。乌克兰虽然夺取了多个村庄，但尚未取得决定性突破。</p><p>基辅的政治和军事领导层抱怨说，西方武器的交付缓慢且不足，使其别无选择，只能在没有足够防空系统的情况下攻击俄罗斯防线，使部队和车辆变得脆弱。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817853?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乌克兰无人机部队的成员检查侦察视频。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817854?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">无人机部队的一名成员正在给降落伞充气，然后将其折叠起来，以便在巴赫穆特附近执行新任务。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌克兰人正在适应并寻求在南部以及东部城市巴赫穆特周围推进， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-hits-a-dead-end-in-bakhmut-1020d4ae?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">这是俄罗斯在冬季和春季攻势中唯一取得的重大进展</a>。为了保护西方装甲，缓慢而谨慎地前进，其中心目标仍然是到达亚速海，切断克里米亚并将俄罗斯军队挤出赫尔松南部地区。</p><p>大多数由西方训练和装备的乌克兰旅仍处于预备役状态，等待攻击。军官们正在寻求保留宝贵的西方装备，从坦克到肩扛式毒刺，同时继续前进。</p><p>哈琴科说：“我们正在用手指试探，并找出拳头应该指向的方向。”</p><p>这位身材魁梧的前伞兵和他的约 100 人连队已准备好突破俄罗斯防线中出现的任何缺口并向南冲去。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=8ADA4C1F-0418-43CF-B08A-6EBE0A657F3A&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">俄罗斯近期的动荡可能为乌克兰战场部队提供机会。 《华尔街日报》记者伊恩·洛维特和退役准将马克·金米特详细分析了乌克兰反攻的下一步行动。图片插图：Jeremy Shuback/《华尔街日报》<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>但差距从未出现。反攻的第三天，他驱车前往奥里希夫东南部的小托克马奇卡，查看他们应该走的路线。当炮弹在他周围轰鸣时，他看到一辆乌克兰车辆被炸毁，乌克兰士兵的尸体散落在路上，他开始撤退。他和他的队友下马去寻找他们能找到的东西。</p><p>现在，任务更加艰巨。 6月初<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-we-know-about-nova-kakhovka-dam-destruction-34bfc197?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">卡霍夫卡​​大坝被毁，</a>第聂伯河被淹没后，俄罗斯将一些守卫该河东岸的部队转移到奥里希夫以南的部队。他们迅速挖土，扩大防线，加固城镇和道路的边缘。</p><p>哈尔琴科和他的部下正在进行训练，以便在南部平坦的土地上逐步推进，那里整洁的村庄点缀在开阔的向日葵和小麦田中。他们使用美国制造的班加罗尔鱼雷和带有炸药的金属杆，他们希望这些鱼雷能够帮助他们清除田野边缘树木上的地雷和诱杀装置，以便他们能够前进和挖掘。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="1198" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/9efe9d94-ec62-45d4-85c6-de057a6a5598-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>他的一名部下质疑，鉴于西方提供了装甲保护，他们为什么要寻求步行前进。</p><p>哈琴科表示，他们不想重蹈俄罗斯在入侵初期所犯的错误，当时乌克兰摧毁了一列又一列的俄罗斯装甲车。</p><p>乌克兰一直用<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-altered-himars-rocket-launchers-to-keep-ukraine-from-firing-missiles-into-russia-11670214338?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">希玛斯火箭炮</a>和远程风暴之影巡航导弹瞄准弹药库和指挥所。 “风暴阴影”攻击距离更远，但价格昂贵且供应短缺，而美国迄今为止拒绝提供可从希马尔发射的远程 ATACMS 导弹。</p><p>因此，乌克兰最近几周采取了更大胆的方式使用“希马尔”导弹，将它们移至距离前线几英里的地方，以深入到被占领土，并将俄罗斯的弹药库和指挥所推得更远。</p><p>美国提供的集束弹药可以帮助炸毁雷区和俄罗斯防御网络，包括战壕和被称为“龙牙”的反坦克障碍物。</p><p>俄罗斯仍然很脆弱，因为其军队总体准备不足，且后勤供应链严重依赖铁路，且供应链薄弱。随着乌克兰向多个地区推进，俄罗斯不知道在哪里部署其后备力量，而且如果乌克兰军队确实突破，俄罗斯可能难以迅速做出反应。</p><p>乌克兰在东部小城巴赫穆特周围的推进速度最快。经过数月的残酷战斗，俄罗斯在五月下旬占领了该城市，导致数千名战士丧生。</p><p>经过几个月的挨家挨户的战斗，俄罗斯人在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/36-hours-in-bakhmut-one-units-desperate-battle-to-hold-back-the-russians-72e30f01?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">占领巴赫穆特</a>后几乎没有时间布设地雷。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/5cd1236f-79b7-4d94-af18-088a71af06de.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>乌克兰发起反击，目前正在将俄罗斯军队击退到该市的北部和南部边缘。在南部，乌克兰军队已经越过一条运河，并正在推进克里什奇夫卡镇，而在北部，他们正在向一条主要高速公路发起进攻。</p><p>与南部地区一样，俄罗斯的空中优势是一个主要障碍。俄罗斯 Ka-52 直升机在距“毒刺”导弹射程约 5 英里的地方盘旋，并向乌克兰目标发射激光制导导弹。</p><p> The West blundered by giving tanks and armored vehicles but insufficient means, such as jet fighters or air-defense systems, to protect them from attack, said Yuriy Ulshyn, a 49-year-old commander near Bakhmut, better known as “Grek,” or “Greek.”</p><p> “It&#39;s like giving a bike without pedals,” said Grek. “Thanks a lot for the bike, but…”</p><p> Grek, a former geologist, commands a unit of some 40 volunteers whom he stations in gaps between larger formations, gluing them together at potential weak points.</p><p> His men on a hillside 3 miles from the edge of Bakhmut are armed with a Stinger and a Soviet-era PKM machine gun, looking out for Russian jets, helicopters and aerial drones. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="928" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/de678d0f-cecd-4389-b108-344d9d47fb10-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Russian Orlan surveillance drones are a constant menace, spotting targets and calling in artillery fire.</p><p> On cloudy days, if the craft swoops low enough, they fire bursts from the PKM, hoping to down it. If the sky is clear, the Russians can watch idly from above the PKM&#39;s range, because Grek&#39;s team is preserving precious Stinger missiles for a more dangerous target like a helicopter or war plane.</p><p> “Our problem everywhere is the sky,” said Grek. “When the enemy can see the whole battlefield, what can you do? You need so much of everything. When he can&#39;t see it, he&#39;s in the dark, and you don&#39;t need as much.”</p><p> The lack of equipment weighs on Grek. A tow rope snapped as he was trying to drag a damaged car away from the front line. Immobilized vehicles, even those in Russian range, are quickly stripped for useful parts. He worries about dying not in the heat of battle, but from his lack of an armored car.</p><p> “I don&#39;t want to die behind the wheel,” Grek said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/ae147933-52d7-446f-9477-641a4ff5948a.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> He and his men are finding creative solutions.</p><p> They scrambled to the top of a slag heap one recent night to mount a camera connected to a Starlink internet terminal powered by a generator. The camera provides a feed that can help them spot Russian aircraft at a distance.</p><p> They make their own attack drones in a garage in a nearby town, equipped with enough explosives to take out an armored vehicle when they slam into them. Their latest innovation, as yet untested in battle, is a remote-controlled machine gun attached to the base of an electric wheelchair.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Do you think Ukraine&#39;s advances around Bakhmut can be sustained?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> In the south, meanwhile, the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/southern-ukrainian-towns-inundated-as-floodwaters-from-burst-dam-rise-7b5e3424?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">flooded Dnipro River</a> has created opportunities by washing away some Russian defenses.</p><p> Ukrainian special forces have crossed the river and are trying to expand a bridgehead opposite the southern capital of Kherson. Other troops have been training in river crossings, including Kharchenko&#39;s men, who used sports inflatables provided by a charity fund.</p><p> Ukraine still holds a morale advantage from fighting for its own territory, Kharchenko said. It may take longer and cost more lives, but “there is no other plan,” he said. “It&#39;s our land. We have to do it.”</p><p> Write to James Marson at <a href="mailto:james.marson@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">james.marson@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a<author><![CDATA[James Marson]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>航空航天/国防</category><category>工业品</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>航天</category><category>防御</category><category>工业品</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Want to Live in London? Write Your Future Landlord a Love Letter]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Renters in the hot market audition with personal statements—including boasts about 5K races—to win over owners; it&#39;s &#39;a dance&#39; <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818845/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="去年伦敦出租的房产。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Properties to let in London last year. HANNAH MCKAY/REUTERS <span>HANNAH MCKAY/REUTERS</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001060029"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001060029"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/josh-mitchell" itemprop="url" rel="author">Josh Mitchell</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/yusuf-khan" itemprop="url" rel="author">Yusuf Khan</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 18, 2023 12:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/london-rental-apartment-landlord-personal-statement-2a4f1a0a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> LONDON—Lola Agabalogun recently responded to an ad for an apartment only to find 100 other renters had called about the same flat in Hackney, one of the city&#39;s trendiest neighborhoods.</p><p> So the 27-year-old ex-New Yorker did what a growing number of other desperate tenants are doing in London these days, and what some landlords are even requiring. She pulled out her laptop and wrote what she described as a love letter to the anonymous landlord, describing how wonderful the flat and neighborhood were. She even mentioned personal details like her love for tennis. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          twocolumn
"><figure class="media-object-image img-twocolumn"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="140" height="185" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818630?width=140&amp;height=185" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The prize</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>不管。 She was outbid to the tune of £400, or about $520, a month.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/renters-are-about-to-get-the-upper-hand-f6387df4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">In New York</a> , “You show up and if you have the right documentation you get the place,” she said. “Here, there is more of a dance.”</p><p> London rentals have been tight since a pandemic <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/london-has-become-the-land-of-the-1-million-home-b610de5f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">surge in home sales</a> took thousands of rental flats out of the city&#39;s already tight supply. Then, hordes of workers and students returned to the city. Average <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/uk-inflation-unexpectedly-held-steady-in-may-as-core-rate-rose-665c7d60?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">rent has soared</a> 49% from the April 2021 pandemic low, according to real estate agency Knight Frank, the second-sharpest growth of any major global city after New York.</p><p> “When the phone started blowing up I actually considered pulling the plug out of the line,” real-estate agent James Dainton said of one particularly hectic period last summer. “I said to the team, &#39;How do we actually deal with 70 to 80 applicants?&#39; We try to be as fair as we can, but at the same time when you&#39;ve got that many inquiries, you&#39;ve got to be a little bit cutthroat.”</p><p> That means raising tenant requirements—including paying multiple months of rent in advance, having family members or friends co-sign the lease and even requiring that tenants tell the landlord a bit about themselves.</p><p> Personal statements, long used by real estate buyers to pull on sellers&#39; heartstrings to win a coveted property, are now part of London&#39;s rental world, used by landlords to discern whether tenants are a good fit, agents said.</p><p> Potential tenants discuss their hobbies, weekend activities, alma maters and other interests, Dainton said. One recent client, an American expat, boasted about his athletic prowess. “He told me he can run a 5K in 15 minutes,” Dainton said. “I was gobsmacked—I can&#39;t get lower than 24 minutes.”</p><p> The runner didn&#39;t get the flat.</p><p> Carman Leung, a 26-year-old recruiter from Sydney, distributed a PDF file to agents that included career highlights, hobbies such as aerial hoop—in which she strikes acrobatic movements from a metal ring suspended in the air—and her ability to speak Spanish and Cantonese. After multiple attempts she found a place, for a rent that was 25% over her budget. She said she wasn&#39;t sure if it was her willingness to pay the price or her note that finally persuaded the landlord. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="700" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818709?width=700&amp;height=700" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Carman Leung wrote about her career and her aerial hoop hobby.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Carman Leung</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Bidding wars are still common, with the person willing to pay the most or take a long-term lease often winning the flat. But some landlords are willing to accept lower rent in exchange for intangible qualities, agents said.</p><p> “It&#39;s like an audition,” said Oliver Cruikshank, director at Keatons, a lettings agency based in East London. “Personality can come into it. If the landlord feels they connect with the tenant they may decide on that, as these two parties are potentially stuck with each other for a long time.”</p><p> He said sometimes “people who usually don&#39;t get no for an answer” are rejected. “People come to us who are earning a quarter of a million a year, and we&#39;re saying we cannot accept their offer,” he said.</p><p> Greg Tsuman, director of the real estate agency Martyn Gerrard, said one client recently showed up to an open house with chocolates and flowers for the landlord. “So, a bribe,” he said half-jokingly.</p><p> Tsuman said landlords themselves are being squeezed. A tax-law change and rising interest rates on mortgages have pushed up landlords&#39; bills in recent years. Many are raising prices out of necessity, he said.</p><p> Tenants and advocacy groups said requiring personal details violates their privacy and increases the risk of discrimination.</p><p> “It was when my friends and I began composing a simpering personal statement just to rent a flat that it finally clicked for me: Britain&#39;s rental market is broken,” a Sunday Times columnist <a href="https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-day-i-realised-the-rental-market-is-broken-qxdnz0w0z" target="_blank" class="icon none">wrote this spring</a> .</p><p> Tom Darling, campaign manager of the advocacy group Renters&#39; Reform Coalition, said the housing crunch has turned London&#39;s property market into the “Wild West.”</p><p> Darling recently toured a dozen rental flats. Landlord agents asked for everything from a biographical essay to a photo. “The estate agent said it was to form a connection with prospective tenants—which is just a recipe for discrimination,” Darling said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818846?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A property to let in the Queen&#39;s Park area of London last year.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Hollie Adams/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> He liked a place, and he debated whether to include in his essay that he had attended Oxford, worrying he might come off as elitist. He included the detail, and mentioned he was in a stable relationship, clean, tidy and career-oriented.</p><p> “It&#39;s slightly degrading, that process of having to sell yourself to find somewhere to live, and you&#39;re trying to think about the ways in which to write your own history,” he said. “The more you put into each application the more liable you are to feel personally about it.”</p><p> In the end, he was outbid on the place.</p><p> Letting agents are also being schmoozed. Freelance writer and Miami native Grazie Sophia Christie moved to London from Boston five years ago and recently searched for a new apartment. She sought old-world charm, but one flat she saw looked more like a frat house. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="700" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818710?width=700&amp;height=700" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Grazie Sophia Christie worked on charming the letting agents.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Grazie Sophia Christie</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “The bedrooms were old and musty,” she said. “Things needed to be repainted. There were stains and broken tiles in the kitchen.”</p><p> When she asked the landlord if he would make the repairs, he scoffed. “He said that he already had an offer,” she said.</p><p> For subsequent flats, she tried a different tactic: implying she was wealthy and flirting with agents.</p><p> “You have to incentivize them to send you a flat before it comes online” and get the letting agent to tell the landlord you are a great future tenant, she said. “You just have to be really friendly and chatter.”</p><p> Write to Josh Mitchell at <a href="mailto:joshua.mitchell@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joshua.mitchell@wsj.com</a> and Yusuf Khan at <a href="mailto:yusuf.khan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">yusuf.khan@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/7014063b-a894-4b50-b6a3-a3b3e88591aa.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/london-rental-apartment-landlord-personal-statement-2a4f1a0a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/london-rental-apartment-landlord-personal-statement-2a4f1a0a<author><![CDATA[Josh MitchellYusuf Khan]]></author><category> wsjfinance</category><category>阿赫德</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>房地产</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>房地产/物业</category><category>Renting/Letting</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>房地产</category><category>财产</category><category>renting</category><category> letting</category><category>建造</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukrainian Strike Disables Bridge Between Crimea and Russia]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Moscow says Kyiv used naval drones to hit only road link from peninsula to Russia <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059347"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=562ED18C-1F7B-4F97-8EEF-A3B2EE57B4D8&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fbridge-between-russia-and-crimea-damaged-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">连接俄罗斯和被占领的克里米亚半岛的刻赤大桥在乌克兰的一次袭击中被毁。俄罗斯表示，基辅使用两架海军无人机袭击了这座桥，该桥是为在乌克兰作战的俄罗斯军队提供补给的重要路线。照片：路透社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059347"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/yaroslav-trofimov" itemprop="url" rel="author">雅罗斯拉夫·特罗菲莫夫</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Updated July 17, 2023 4:04 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge-between-russia-and-crimea-damaged-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>乌克兰的一次袭击使连接俄罗斯与被占领的克里米亚半岛的唯一公路桥瘫痪，再次打击了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>总统统治的一个主要象征，并限制了俄罗斯对乌克兰南部<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-counteroffensive-frontlines-russia-add3e4e4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">前线的</a>供应。</p><p> Russian Deputy Prime Minister Marat Khusnullin said it would likely take until mid-September to restore partial two-way cargo traffic on the bridge, and until November to fully rebuild the 12-mile-long structure.</p><p> According to Russia&#39;s National Antiterrorism Committee, Kyiv used two naval drones against <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/attack-on-russias-kerch-bridge-hits-crucial-link-for-crimea-and-troops-11665342526?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the bridge</a> , hitting it at around 3 am local time on Monday.乌克兰媒体援引政府消息人士的话称，海军无人机也参与其中。</p><p>乌克兰 SBU 情报部门发言人 Artem Degtyarenko 告诉乌克兰国际文传电讯社，有关袭击组织方式的所有细节将在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-gears-up-to-hit-russiansand-show-west-it-can-win-89c43105?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰获胜</a>后公布。 “Any illegal structures used to deliver Russian instruments of mass murder are necessarily short-lived,” said Mykhailo Podolyak, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky&#39;s adviser. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="908" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/d0587735-f4b2-487c-afa7-3aaa47c344b7-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Coming in the middle of Crimea&#39;s tourism season, Monday&#39;s strikes inflicted yet another blow to Putin&#39;s prestige in addition to creating formidable logistical hurdles for the Russian war effort. Built at a cost of $4 billion after Russia <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/vladimir-putin-signs-treaty-to-annex-crimea-1395144516?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">annexed Crimea</a> in 2014, the bridge has become a major symbol of Putin&#39;s drive to wash away the humiliation he says had been inflicted on Russia by the Soviet Union&#39;s collapse. Putin personally opened it in 2018.</p><p> Ukraine already <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/major-explosion-hits-the-bridge-between-crimea-and-russia-halting-traffic-11665215052?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">damaged the bridge</a> once, last October, just hours after Putin&#39;s birthday. At the time, only one of the two road parts of the bridge collapsed, and alternating traffic on the second two-lane part resumed hours later.</p><p> Khusnullin, who inspected the site Monday and reported to Putin, said that the bridge&#39;s pillars haven&#39;t been damaged, but that one span will have to be completely replaced. A parallel span, he said, has been displaced by some 70-80 centimeters but still rests on a pillar. Repair crews are trying to fix it in place and will test it initially with vehicles up to three tons, the weight of a passenger car, and then up to five tons, the weight of an average ambulance, hoping to reopen the lane for limited use. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818349?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A military helicopter flying over damaged parts of the Kerch Bridge.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>The separate rail bridge, which sustained serious damage in October, was only lightly damaged in Monday&#39;s blasts, Khusnullin said. Rail services, which are more important for military supplies, have already resumed.</p><p> John Kirby, a spokesman for the White House National Security Council, said he doubted the strike would have a major impact on Russia&#39;s warfighting capacity, noting the Russians have many other ways to supply forces in the Crimean Peninsula.</p><p> Russia said two civilians died on the bridge. “This is yet another terrorist act of the Kyiv regime,” Putin said at the end of a videoconference with government officials on the consequences of the attack. “A Russian response will occur. The ministry of defense is preparing proposals accordingly.”</p><p> Putin responded to the October attack by ordering <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-ukraine-survived-russias-mission-to-turn-off-the-lights-winter-is-over-and-were-still-here-8668c5f5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">waves of strikes</a> on Ukrainian civilian infrastructure that aimed to deprive Ukrainians of electricity, heating and water during the winter.这些攻击虽然导致轮流停电，但最终未能摧毁该国的能源系统，同时促使美国及其盟国向乌克兰提供现代防空系统，例如爱国者和SAMP-T反导弹系统。</p><p>乌克兰上个月在乌克兰南部发动攻势，但由于其部队面临大片雷区和防御工事以及俄罗斯武装直升机，因此只取得了有限的进展。最近几周，基辅利用英国和法国提供的“风暴之影”和“头皮” <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-deadly-new-missile-was-created-to-hit-saddam-hussein-in-his-bathtub-75e04412?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">巡航导弹</a>，大大扩展了其射程，重点摧毁俄罗斯武器库、指挥中心和后勤节点。</p><p>上个月，“风暴之影”袭击了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-strikes-bridge-supplying-russian-troops-56564b0b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">琼哈尔大桥，</a>克里米亚和乌克兰南部之间的主要连接被切断了十天，这条替代道路现在已成为俄罗斯的主要生命线。琼哈尔大桥于7月3日重新开放。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="479" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818163?width=700&amp;height=479" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">据报道，这张图片显示了连接俄罗斯和克里米亚的桥梁受损情况。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：OSTOROZHNO NOVOSTI/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>去年秋天，乌克兰成功地运用了这一战略，当时对第聂伯河上的桥梁和其他后勤节点的袭击将俄罗斯军队赶出了被占领的南部城市赫尔松。</p><p>周一的袭击发生当天，俄罗斯、土耳其、联合国和乌克兰之间允许乌克兰港口出口谷物和其他食品的协议即将到期。该协议一年前在伊斯坦布尔达成，此后定期更新。袭击发生后，俄罗斯表示<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-says-it-is-pulling-out-of-ukraine-grain-deal-68190d1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">将退出该协议</a>，但谈判仍在继续，土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安表示，他计划与普京讨论延期事宜。自去年8月该协议生效以来，乌克兰出口了超过3200万吨粮食。</p><p>去年二月，随着普京入侵乌克兰，与克里米亚的民用航空联系中断。通过乌克兰南部赫尔松、扎波罗热和顿涅茨克地区被占领地区的车辙道路与俄罗斯的替代连接非常复杂，而且在某些地区相对靠近前线。</p><p> With tens of thousands of tourists stranded in Crimea, the Russian government said that it will relax border checks and abolish the curfew along the alternative roads in occupied southern Ukraine. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="435" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818168?width=700&amp;height=435" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">交通暂停后，警察封锁了通往刻赤海峡一座桥梁的道路。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Sergei Malgavko/TASS/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>写信给雅罗斯拉夫·特罗菲莫夫 (yaroslav Trofimov)： <a href="mailto:yaroslav.trofimov@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">yaroslav.trofimov@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 20:04:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge- Between- Russia-and-crimea-damaging-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge- Between- Russia-and-crimea-damaging-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88<author><![CDATA[Yaroslav Trofimov]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>重型建筑</category><category>桥梁建设</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>海军</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>弗拉基米尔普京</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>海军</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>heavy construction</category><category>桥梁建设</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukrainian Strike Disables Bridge Between Crimea and Russia]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Moscow says Kyiv used naval drones to hit only road link from peninsula to Russia <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059347"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=562ED18C-1F7B-4F97-8EEF-A3B2EE57B4D8&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fbridge-between-russia-and-crimea-damaged-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">连接俄罗斯和被占领的克里米亚半岛的刻赤大桥在乌克兰的一次袭击中被毁。俄罗斯表示，基辅使用两架海军无人机袭击了这座桥，该桥是为在乌克兰作战的俄罗斯军队提供补给的重要路线。照片：路透社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059347"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/yaroslav-trofimov" itemprop="url" rel="author">雅罗斯拉夫·特罗菲莫夫</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Updated July 17, 2023 4:04 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge-between-russia-and-crimea-damaged-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>乌克兰的一次袭击使连接俄罗斯与被占领的克里米亚半岛的唯一公路桥瘫痪，再次打击了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">弗拉基米尔·普京</a>总统统治的一个主要象征，并限制了俄罗斯对乌克兰南部<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-counteroffensive-frontlines-russia-add3e4e4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">前线的</a>供应。</p><p> Russian Deputy Prime Minister Marat Khusnullin said it would likely take until mid-September to restore partial two-way cargo traffic on the bridge, and until November to fully rebuild the 12-mile-long structure.</p><p> According to Russia&#39;s National Antiterrorism Committee, Kyiv used two naval drones against <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/attack-on-russias-kerch-bridge-hits-crucial-link-for-crimea-and-troops-11665342526?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the bridge</a> , hitting it at around 3 am local time on Monday.乌克兰媒体援引政府消息人士的话称，海军无人机也参与其中。</p><p>乌克兰 SBU 情报部门发言人 Artem Degtyarenko 告诉乌克兰国际文传电讯社，有关袭击组织方式的所有细节将在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-gears-up-to-hit-russiansand-show-west-it-can-win-89c43105?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰获胜</a>后公布。 “Any illegal structures used to deliver Russian instruments of mass murder are necessarily short-lived,” said Mykhailo Podolyak, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky&#39;s adviser. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="908" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/d0587735-f4b2-487c-afa7-3aaa47c344b7-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Coming in the middle of Crimea&#39;s tourism season, Monday&#39;s strikes inflicted yet another blow to Putin&#39;s prestige in addition to creating formidable logistical hurdles for the Russian war effort. Built at a cost of $4 billion after Russia <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/vladimir-putin-signs-treaty-to-annex-crimea-1395144516?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">annexed Crimea</a> in 2014, the bridge has become a major symbol of Putin&#39;s drive to wash away the humiliation he says had been inflicted on Russia by the Soviet Union&#39;s collapse. Putin personally opened it in 2018.</p><p> Ukraine already <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/major-explosion-hits-the-bridge-between-crimea-and-russia-halting-traffic-11665215052?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">damaged the bridge</a> once, last October, just hours after Putin&#39;s birthday. At the time, only one of the two road parts of the bridge collapsed, and alternating traffic on the second two-lane part resumed hours later.</p><p> Khusnullin, who inspected the site Monday and reported to Putin, said that the bridge&#39;s pillars haven&#39;t been damaged, but that one span will have to be completely replaced. A parallel span, he said, has been displaced by some 70-80 centimeters but still rests on a pillar. Repair crews are trying to fix it in place and will test it initially with vehicles up to three tons, the weight of a passenger car, and then up to five tons, the weight of an average ambulance, hoping to reopen the lane for limited use. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818349?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A military helicopter flying over damaged parts of the Kerch Bridge.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>The separate rail bridge, which sustained serious damage in October, was only lightly damaged in Monday&#39;s blasts, Khusnullin said. Rail services, which are more important for military supplies, have already resumed.</p><p> John Kirby, a spokesman for the White House National Security Council, said he doubted the strike would have a major impact on Russia&#39;s warfighting capacity, noting the Russians have many other ways to supply forces in the Crimean Peninsula.</p><p> Russia said two civilians died on the bridge. “This is yet another terrorist act of the Kyiv regime,” Putin said at the end of a videoconference with government officials on the consequences of the attack. “A Russian response will occur. The ministry of defense is preparing proposals accordingly.”</p><p> Putin responded to the October attack by ordering <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-ukraine-survived-russias-mission-to-turn-off-the-lights-winter-is-over-and-were-still-here-8668c5f5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">waves of strikes</a> on Ukrainian civilian infrastructure that aimed to deprive Ukrainians of electricity, heating and water during the winter.这些攻击虽然导致轮流停电，但最终未能摧毁该国的能源系统，同时促使美国及其盟国向乌克兰提供现代防空系统，例如爱国者和SAMP-T反导弹系统。</p><p>乌克兰上个月在乌克兰南部发动攻势，但由于其部队面临大片雷区和防御工事以及俄罗斯武装直升机，因此只取得了有限的进展。最近几周，基辅利用英国和法国提供的“风暴之影”和“头皮” <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraines-deadly-new-missile-was-created-to-hit-saddam-hussein-in-his-bathtub-75e04412?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">巡航导弹</a>，大大扩展了其射程，重点摧毁俄罗斯武器库、指挥中心和后勤节点。</p><p>上个月，“风暴之影”袭击了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-strikes-bridge-supplying-russian-troops-56564b0b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">琼哈尔大桥，</a>克里米亚和乌克兰南部之间的主要连接被切断了十天，这条替代道路现在已成为俄罗斯的主要生命线。琼哈尔大桥于7月3日重新开放。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="479" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818163?width=700&amp;height=479" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">据报道，这张图片显示了连接俄罗斯和克里米亚的桥梁受损情况。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：OSTOROZHNO NOVOSTI/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>去年秋天，乌克兰成功地运用了这一战略，当时对第聂伯河上的桥梁和其他后勤节点的袭击将俄罗斯军队赶出了被占领的南部城市赫尔松。</p><p>周一的袭击发生当天，俄罗斯、土耳其、联合国和乌克兰之间允许乌克兰港口出口谷物和其他食品的协议即将到期。该协议一年前在伊斯坦布尔达成，此后定期更新。袭击发生后，俄罗斯表示<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-says-it-is-pulling-out-of-ukraine-grain-deal-68190d1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">将退出该协议</a>，但谈判仍在继续，土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安表示，他计划与普京讨论延期事宜。自去年8月该协议生效以来，乌克兰出口了超过3200万吨粮食。</p><p>去年二月，随着普京入侵乌克兰，与克里米亚的民用航空联系中断。通过乌克兰南部赫尔松、扎波罗热和顿涅茨克地区被占领地区的车辙道路与俄罗斯的替代连接非常复杂，而且在某些地区相对靠近前线。</p><p> With tens of thousands of tourists stranded in Crimea, the Russian government said that it will relax border checks and abolish the curfew along the alternative roads in occupied southern Ukraine. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="435" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818168?width=700&amp;height=435" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">交通暂停后，警察封锁了通往刻赤海峡一座桥梁的道路。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Sergei Malgavko/TASS/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>写信给雅罗斯拉夫·特罗菲莫夫 (yaroslav Trofimov)： <a href="mailto:yaroslav.trofimov@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">yaroslav.trofimov@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 20:04:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge- Between- Russia-and-crimea-damaging-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bridge- Between- Russia-and-crimea-damaging-in-overnight-strike-a3431b88<author><![CDATA[Yaroslav Trofimov]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>重型建筑</category><category>桥梁建设</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>海军</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>弗拉基米尔普京</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>海军</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>heavy construction</category><category>桥梁建设</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Netanyahu Faces Fresh Standoff With Israeli Reservists Over Judicial Overhaul]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>精英预备役空军飞行员表示，如果政府通过一项他们认为对民主构成威胁的法律，他们可能会停止服役<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001060226"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818264?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">战斗机飞行员在以色列频繁的军事行动中发挥着至关重要的作用。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Abir Sultan/EPA-EFE/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001060226"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dov-lieber" itemprop="url" rel="author">多夫·利伯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 17 日上午 11:57 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-faces-fresh-stand-off-with-israeli-reservists-over-judicial-overhaul-b974d3f5"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>特拉维夫——以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡本周将推动旨在改革国家司法系统的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-revives-judicial-overhaul-stripped-of-most-controversial-piece-33160de?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">有争议的立法，</a>并与该国的一群预备役军人进行第二次摊牌。</p><p> 1000多名预备役军人考虑停止服役，其中包括数百名精锐预备役空军飞行员，如果政府通过立法，他们认为这对国家民主构成威胁，并使他们面临接受不负责任领导人命令的风险。三月份的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-israels-citizen-soldiers-forced-netanyahu-to-retreat-on-judicial-overhaul-21d55e4e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">类似对峙</a>引发了全国性的风暴，最终迫使内塔尼亚胡搁置了改革。随后与反对派的妥协谈判上个月陷入僵局。</p><p>战斗机飞行员在以色列频繁的军事行动中发挥着至关重要的作用，使该国陷入内塔尼亚胡政府与该国一些最受尊敬的公民士兵之间的危险冲突。</p><p>内塔尼亚胡在六月下旬接受《华尔街日报》采访时表示，他将推进改革，但会<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-revives-judicial-overhaul-stripped-of-most-controversial-piece-33160de?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">取消一项赋予国家立法机构推翻最高法院裁决权力的条款</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="426" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818282?width=639&amp;height=426" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以色列国防部长约阿夫·加兰特与高级军事官员讨论了预备役抗议可能产生的影响。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：吉尔·科恩-马根/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>以色列议会最早可能于周日就一项修订后的法案进行投票，该法案将限制最高法院以合理性为由否决政府或民选官员决策的能力，批评者称这一术语过于模糊，并允许法院出于政治目的推翻民选官员的意愿。包括预备役军人在内的反对这项立法的人认为，这将取消对行政部门权力的重要制衡。</p><p>新的斗争凸显了自内塔尼亚胡联盟<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-right-wing-lawmakers-aim-to-remake-supreme-court-11668506325?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">开始推行削弱最高法院并赋予民选官员更多权力的计划</a>以来数月来加剧的深刻政治紧张局势。连续27周吸引数十万以色列人走上街头的大规模抗议活动背后<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-judicial-reforms-could-strengthen-religions-role-in-public-life-11674476463?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，是对内塔尼亚胡政府走向的担忧</a>。分析人士称，内塔尼亚胡政府是该国历史上最右翼、最虔诚的政府。</p><p>军事分析人士表示，以色列军队的核心是义务兵和军官，但它严重依赖广泛的预备役军人。在精锐部队服役的军官在完成义务服役后，每年通常会被征召服役一个月。</p><p>与大多数预备役军人不同，飞行员必须每月多次参加严格的训练演习，而且他们往往是以色列高度活跃的军队所开展的任何行动中不可或缺的一部分。</p><p>两名带头参加空军抗议活动的前空军军官表示，上周与法律专家会面后，数百名后备飞行员表示，如果政府通过该法案，他们正在考虑不去上班。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818265?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">反对拟议的司法改革的抗议活动（就像本月在海法发生的那样）已吸引数十万以色列人走上街头。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Matan Golan/SOPA/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>新一轮的内部对峙发生在该国的敏感时刻。伊朗正在推动其在该地区的盟友攻击以色列，以色列安全官员警告说，其北部边境与伊朗支持的黎巴嫩激进分子和政治组织真主党之间的紧张局势可能引发地区战争。</p><p> “他们不得不采取这种极端措施，因为似乎没有其他办法。这是最后的手段，”机长盖伊·波兰（Guy Poran）说，他是飞行员抗议运动的领导人之一。</p><p>除了战斗机飞行员之外，包括来自军队情报部队和突击队在内的 1000 多名其他预备役军人最近几天也签署了给指挥官的信函，威胁如果政府开始通过部分司法改革，他们将停止服役。</p><p> “面对政府最近正在推进的立法程序……虽然完全无视这项立法正在破坏以色列社会的共同基础并撕裂国家，但我们的良心不允许我们袖手旁观，”一封由以色列人签署的信中写道。超过 300 名预备役军人被送往以色列最精锐、最秘密的突击队指挥官马特卡尔 (Sayeret Matkal)，内塔尼亚胡是该部队的校友。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D95FB00D-DFCE-4B6E-9B89-889EB0968CE4&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fnetanyahu-faces-fresh-stand-off-with-israeli-reservists-over-judicial-overhaul-b974d3f5&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡与《华尔街日报》记者多夫·利伯坐下来讨论该国面临的大规模抗议活动、约旦河西岸不断恶化的安全局势以及来自伊朗不断升级的威胁。照片：Dror Lebendiger for The Wall Street Journal<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>内塔尼亚胡周一在内阁会议上表示，那些拒绝服役的人违反了法律。</p><p>他补充说，改变有关使用合理性的法律会破坏以色列民主的想法“脱离了现实，纯粹是为了吓唬人们”。内塔尼亚胡说：“在民主国家，军队服从民选政府，而不是相反。”</p><p>抗议的预备役军人表示，只有那些处于预备役义务阶段的人才会威胁拒绝服役。</p><p>周日晚上，以色列国防部长约阿夫·加兰特会见了以色列军事参谋长赫兹·哈勒维以及空军、海军、情报局和其他高级军事官员，讨论了预备役军人抗议活动可能产生的影响和两名国防官员表示，如果他们的威胁得到落实，将会发生什么。</p><p>以色列军方表示，目前预备役军人未到岗的事件“非常有限”。</p><p>抗议的预备役军人声称，内塔尼亚胡通过的立法将促进独裁统治，并将前所未有的权力交给以色列许多人认为由宗教极端分子领导的政府，从而威胁以色列的民主。</p><p> 63 岁的伞兵预备役上校盖尔·努法尔 (Gal Nufar) 表示，经过数月的深思熟虑、彻夜难眠，并担心自己可能会收到一个权力不受制衡的政府下达的非法命令，他上周决定停止志愿参加预备役。</p><p> “本来我觉得做这样的事就等于背叛军队。但在过去的几个月里，我看到他们把我们带到了我最害怕的地步……政权政变不允许对政府进行任何平衡或任何制衡，”他说。</p><p>曾担任战斗机飞行员 30 年、现在在国防部履行预备役义务的 Ophir Bear 上校表示，飞行员担心他们可能会被命令采取非法行动，并且以色列法院可能不再被视为独立该立法通过后，士兵很容易受到国际刑事法院的起诉。</p><p>一些抗议的预备役军人表示，他们认为司法改革带来的威胁甚至比来自外敌的外部威胁更严重。</p><p>努法尔说：“在我看来，来自真主党和伊朗的威胁是严重的，但这根本不等于我们在该国面临的内部威胁。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818276?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以色列总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡本月访问一个空军基地时表示，拒绝服役的人违反了法律。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ABIR SULTAN/EPA-EFE/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>盖·波兰 (Guy Poran) 是飞行员抗议运动的领导人。本文的早期版本将他的姓氏错误地拼写为 Poren。 （7月17日更正）</p><p>写信给 Dov Lieber，邮箱为<a href="mailto:dov.lieber@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dov.lieber@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 15:57:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-faces-fresh-stand-off-with-israeli-reservists-over-judicial-overhaul-b974d3f5</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/netanyahu-faces-fresh-stand-off-with-israeli-reservists-over-judicial-overhaul-b974d3f5<author><![CDATA[Dov Lieber]]></author><category>空军</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>本杰明·内塔尼亚胡</category><category>空军</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Singapore, Known for Clean Government, Rocked by Graft Probe, Resignations]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>城邦国家总理寻求修复因涉及执政党政客的泄密事件而造成的损失<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001060129"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="574" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818364?width=860&amp;height=574" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">新加坡总理李显龙表示，该党的两名议员因“不正当关系”而辞去立法会职务。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Anupam Nath/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001060129"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/chunhan-wong" itemprop="url" rel="author">黄春汉</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 17 日上午 11:21 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/singapore-known-for-clean-government-rocked-by-graft-probe-resignations-2b8d703d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>新加坡——自新加坡近六十年前建国以来，对于执政党来说，这是艰难的一个月。</p><p>一项高层腐败调查以及两名执政党议员因婚外情辞职震惊了这个东南亚城邦，那里的政治精英将其合法性建立在政府廉洁和道德正直的声誉之上。</p><p>周一，新加坡总理表示，人民行动党的两名议员，包括议长，因两人之间“不正当关系”而辞去立法机关和党内职务。总理办公室公布了两位议员的辞职信，他们在信中道歉。他们没有立即回应置评请求。</p><p>一周前，新加坡反腐败机构逮捕了交通部长和一位人脉广泛的亿万富翁，接受讯问，这是该国近四十年来最<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/singapore-minister-billionaire-hotelier-questioned-in-rare-corruption-probe-df1f8b62?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">引人注目的腐败调查</a>。</p><p>当局尚未指控部长 S. Iswaran 或亿万富翁酒店老板 Ong Beng Seng 有不当行为，这两人已被保释。伊斯瓦兰没有回应询问，而翁的发言人拒绝发表评论。</p><p>此前，公众对另外两名政府部长及其租赁国有豪华平房的行为表示强烈抗议，这一事件引发了有关新加坡财富不平等的辩论，并引发了对这两名部长在租赁方面是否存在不当行为的反腐败审查。的属性。六月结束的审查清除了部长们的任何不当行为。</p><p>新加坡领导人寻求迅速修复损害，重申对腐败的零容忍立场，并向公民保证执政党将惩罚官员和成员的任何不当行为。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818295?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">新加坡反腐败机构最近逮捕了该国交通部长易瓦兰 (S. Iswaran)，以在腐败调查中接受讯问；当局尚未指控该部长有不当行为，他已被保释。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：罗斯兰·拉赫曼/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>总理李显龙周一表示：“高标准的礼节和个人行为，以及保持廉洁和廉洁，是新加坡人信任和尊重人民行动党并授权我们组建政府的根本原因。”</p><p>李承认，该党处理高级成员的不当行为可能会“在政治上令人尴尬且代价高昂”。 “任何制度都不可能是完全无误的，”总理说。 “有时候事情会出错，你必须找出来并纠正它。”</p><p>在新加坡，涉及高级执政党成员的腐败和其他不当行为的指控很少见，新加坡享有廉洁声誉，这使得这个东南亚金融中心成为世界各地投资者的宠儿。腐败监管机构透明国际将新加坡评为 2022 年亚洲腐败程度最低的国家，在全球排名第五，仅次于丹麦、芬兰、新西兰和挪威。</p><p>当地官员表示，新加坡之所以能做到如此廉洁，部分原因在于向政府部长支付高薪，初级部长的年薪可能超过 80 万美元。官员们表示，这种做法有助于减少滥用权力谋取个人利益的动机，从而有助于预防腐败。</p><p>政治分析人士表示，最近的一波指控可能会削弱民众对执政党的支持。 “这对人民行动党来说是一场完美的风暴。该党正面临最严重的政治危机，公众的信任和信心面临着真正受到侵蚀的风险。”</p>新加坡管理大学法学副教授。<p></p><p>陈说，人民行动党“被认为没有达到其高标准，这不再是一个值得怀疑的因素，而是一个合理的问题，也是新加坡人真正关心的问题”。</p><p>自新加坡 1965 年成为独立国家以来，人民行动党一直在新加坡掌权，在周一辞职后，该党仍然在议会中占据主导地位。它的立法机构有 80 名议员，有 93 个选举席位，其中包括交通部长，总理已指示他在腐败调查继续期间休假。</p><p>主要反对党工人党目前有九名民选立法委员。另外，周一，工人党表示，正在调查一段视频，该视频暗示两名高级党员之间存在“不当交流”，该视频似乎显示一男一女在餐厅里牵手，该视频在社交媒体上流传。这两名成员（其中一名是议员）没有立即回应置评请求。</p><p>过去，人民行动党和工人党的议员都因面临婚外情指控而辞职或被解职。</p><p>周一，李总理表示国会议长陈川镇和议员郑立辉</p>两人之间存在着“不正当关系”，这种关系在总理二月份建议他们停止后仍在继续。据总理称，陈随后提出辞呈，李明博允许议长暂时留任，为他的离职做准备。李说，他最近了解到的信息“强烈表明，尽管有他的干预，但这种关系仍在继续”，此后他决定谭必须立即离开。 <p></p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818369?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">新加坡总理表示，曾在 2013 年的一次活动中挥舞旗帜的前政府部长陈川进 (Tan Chuan Jin) 已辞去立法机关职务。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：soe Than win/法新社/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>立法选举要到 2025 年才会举行，李总理周一表示，他不打算立即举行投票。两位即将卸任的执政党议员留下的空缺将由其所在选区的其他议员填补，这些议员被称为“团体代表选区”，议员团队集体选举产生席位。</p><p>即便如此，人民行动党可能会在未来几个月面临对其受欢迎程度的考验，届时新加坡将选举下一任礼仪性国家元首。执政党青睐的候选人、前资政尚达曼已宣布竞选总统。其他潜在候选人也表示有参选的兴趣。那些寻求竞选的人仍然必须获得政府指定的评估总统职位资格的小组的批准。</p><p>如果不晚于9月举行总统选举，尚达曼以微弱优势获胜，甚至其他候选人获胜，都会成为对执政党的谴责。分析人士表示，这样的结果可能会促使执政党采取更多措施来安抚公众对收入不平等、房价上涨和高生活成本等问题的不满。</p><p>写信给 Chun Han Wong： <a href="mailto:chunhan.wong@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">chunhan.wong@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 15:21:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/singapore-known-for-clean-government-rocked-by-graft-probe-resignations-2b8d703d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/singapore-known-for-clean-government-rocked-by-graft-probe-resignations-2b8d703d<author><![CDATA[Chun Han Wong]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>政治任命/终止</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>政治任命</category><category>终止</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China Sets Heat Record as John Kerry Arrives to Discuss Climate]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>预计持续数周的热浪将导致西北地区气温超过 120 华氏度<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059875"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818293?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">中国首都北京的一名工人连续26天气温超过104度。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Andy Wong/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059875"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sha-hua" itemprop="url" rel="author">沙华</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 17 日上午 9:37 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-sets-heat-record-as-john-kerry-arrives-to-discuss-climate-6a35c686"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>新加坡——就在美国气候特使约翰·克里抵达北京试图<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/at-cop27-poorer-countries-secure-climate-damage-fund-without-pledging-faster-emissions-cuts-11668947145?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">重振全球两个最大排放国之间陷入僵局的气候变化合作</a>的同一天，中国一个村庄的气温达到了华氏 126 度，创下该国有记录以来的最高温度。二氧化碳。</p><p>据官方媒体报道，这一纪录于周日在中国西北部新疆地区吐鲁番市郊外的一个偏远乡镇三堡创下。吐鲁番盆地是一个面积达 19,000 平方英里的沙丘盆地，湖床干涸，另外四个乡镇的气温也超过了 122 度。</p><p>近几天来，热浪<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/weeks-of-extreme-heat-strain-small-businesses-and-economy-add05101?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">席卷全球</a>。超过 1 亿美国人正遭受<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/dangerous-heat-wave-broils-southern-u-s-87f1f969?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">覆盖南部和西南部的</a>连续 110 华氏度的高温，而极端高温<a href="https://www.wsj.com/video/heat-wave-hits-italy-spain-and-greece-temperatures-above-111-degrees/9AEFE6BB-14B5-4D45-ACBD-0E0D834E17F4.html?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">席卷了意大利、西班牙和希腊</a>。上周是地球有记录以来最热的一周，紧接着是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/june-hottest-on-record-heat-b222c05c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">有记录以来最热的六月</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818290?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">美国气候特使约翰·克里周一在北京受到了中国气候变化特使解振华的迎接。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：VALERIE VOLCOVICI/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>中国官员警告说，随着气候变化加速，中国特别容易受到气温上升的影响。中国气象协会本月发布的今年《中国气候变化蓝皮书》显示，自上世纪初以来，中国年平均气温每十年上升0.16摄氏度，高于全球平均水平。</p><p>今年夏天，中国大片地区遭遇酷暑，预计这波浪潮将持续到月底。 Many cities have turned air-raid shelters, which can be nearly 20 degrees Fahrenheit cooler than outside, into refuges for residents trying to escape the heat, state media said.</p><p> Local governments instructed people in affected areas to avoid outdoor activities and reduce their work hours if they had to work outside in the heat. Chinese media haven&#39;t reported any human deaths from this current heat wave but said more than 4,000 chickens and 462 pigs <a href="https://www.globaltimes.cn/page/202307/1294140.shtml" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">perished in the heat</a> last week after power failures. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818291?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A mist machine offered relief from high temperatures in Shanghai last week.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ying Tang/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The Paris Agreement set a goal of limiting global warming since the preindustrial era to well under 2 degrees Celsius and preferably to 1.5 degrees. Climate experts warn that it is increasingly likely global temperatures <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-warming-likely-to-pass-1-5-degree-threshold-in-next-five-years-u-n-report-says-a829b40b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">will breach the 1.5 degrees Celsius threshold</a> , and that mitigating the worst effects of climate change will require the US and China to work together.</p><p> Climate talks between the US and China ground to a halt after then-House Speaker <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/nancy-pelosi">Nancy Pelosi</a> &#39;s trip to Taiwan last summer but were revived three months later on the sidelines of the annual climate gathering in Egypt.</p><p> Kerry is expected to spend three days in Beijing in an effort to reboot climate cooperation between Beijing and Washington on several pressing issues, including the reduction of coal use and emissions of methane, a greenhouse gas that escapes during gas and oil production. The two sides are also expected to discuss technical issues to prepare the ground before the next climate summit, in Dubai at the end of the year.</p><p> Kerry spent four hours on Monday meeting with his Chinese counterpart Xie Zhenhua in the Beijing Hotel near the Forbidden City, according to state broadcaster China Central Television. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818292?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Visitors coped with the heat on a visit to the Forbidden City in Beijing this month.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: greg baker/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> China has been combating extreme weather all year. In January, a city in northeastern China saw temperatures plummet as low as minus 63 degrees Fahrenheit. Heavy rains devastated wheat fields in central China in May and Beijing, the capital, has been facing one of its hottest summers on record, with temperatures soaring past 104 degrees for 26 consecutive days.</p><p> Some experts say this year&#39;s heat waves might stem in part from El Niño, a hard-to-predict climate pattern caused by warming of ocean surface temperatures in the Pacific Ocean, which could lead to a surge in global temperatures and disruptive weather and climate patterns.</p><p> Last year, scorching heat and record-low rainfall in August <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-scorching-heat-and-hydropower-missteps-test-nations-power-grid-11661514473?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">led to power shortages in China</a> , which damaged crop yields, forced offices to shut down and led to the temporary suspension of plant operations for Toyota, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/XE/XETR/VOW" class="company-name">Volkswagen</a> and some suppliers for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="company-name">Apple</a> supplier <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TW/XTAI/2317" class="">Foxconn</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span> </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=9AEFE6BB-14B5-4D45-ACBD-0E0D834E17F4&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchina-sets-heat-record-as-john-kerry-arrives-to-discuss-climate-6a35c686&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> A heat wave is sweeping across Europe with temperatures reaching the triple-digits in Italy, Spain and Greece. In the US, extreme heat warnings remain in place across Southern states with temperatures set to break records. Photo: Remo Casilli/Reuters<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Write to Sha Hua at <a href="mailto:sha.hua@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sha.hua@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 13:37:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-sets-heat-record-as-john-kerry-arrives-to-discuss-climate-6a35c686</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-sets-heat-record-as-john-kerry-arrives-to-discuss-climate-6a35c686<author><![CDATA[Sha Hua]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>Global/World Issues</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>天气</category><category>Routine Weather Reports</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>日常新闻</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>约翰·克里</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>气候变化</category><category>国际关系</category><category>自然环境</category><category>全球的</category><category>world issues</category><category>政治</category><category>天气</category><category>routine weather reports</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>常规新闻</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China’s Fading Recovery Tests Policy Makers’ Playbook]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> The country&#39;s post-Covid rebound peters out, endangering Beijing&#39;s relatively conservative growth target of around 5% <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059577"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817249?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Many economists say that to boost its economy, China should provide more direct support to individual consumers.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cfoto/DDP/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001059577"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/stella-yifan-xie" itemprop="url" rel="author">Stella Yifan Xie</a></span> in Hong Kong and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jason-douglas" itemprop="url" rel="author">Jason Douglas</a></span> in Singapore</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 17, 2023 8:06 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-fading-recovery-tests-policy-makers-economic-playbook-8ce334f9"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> More stimulus is on the way to boost China&#39;s sputtering economy, economists say. Just not the kind the country needs.</p><p> China&#39;s economy got a fresh dose of bad news on Monday, with <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-barely-grows-as-recovery-fades-5652a92a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">growth in the second quarter of the year slowing to 0.8%</a> when compared with the prior quarter—losing steam just months after <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-covid-dropped-restrictions-reopen-xi-11673534796?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">lifting strict Covid-19 measures</a> that had suppressed the economy for the better part of three years.</p><p> The fading recovery has raised expectations that Chinese officials will unveil limited new measures to juice growth soon, including interest rate cuts and more easing in the housing market, in a bid to combat the rising risk of deflation and growing signs of weak confidence among consumers and businesses.</p><p> The country&#39;s gross domestic product grew by 6.3% in the second quarter when compared with a year earlier, up from the 4.5% growth rate in the first quarter. But that healthy-looking figure was aided by a comparison to a period last year when Covid lockdowns were hammering supply chains and bringing almost all economic activity to a halt. It was also far weaker than the 6.9% expected by economists polled by The Wall Street Journal.</p><p> Other troubling signs included <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-problem-that-wont-go-away-in-china-high-youth-unemployment-f22e3b8c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">youth unemployment</a> rising to a record high in June, while retail sales inched up just 0.2% from May. Beijing&#39;s full-year growth target of around 5%—once viewed as conservative—is now at risk unless authorities respond with more forceful measures, economists say.</p><p> The problem for Chinese policy makers is that injecting more credit into the market and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-banks-cut-rates-to-spur-economic-growth-11661151854?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">cutting interest rates modestly</a> , as they have been doing in recent months, is likely to have little effect, since <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fueled-by-long-credit-binge-chinas-economy-faces-drag-from-debt-purge-e4621859?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">few businesses and families want to borrow</a> to finance investment or spending. Beijing&#39;s traditional playbook for propping up growth—by spending on infrastructure and supporting manufacturers, rather than focusing on households—is also yielding diminishing returns.</p><p> Instead, China should provide more direct support to individual consumers, many economists say.</p><p> There is an expectation that “once you get into a deflationary environment with weak confidence, that will prompt the officials to do more,” said Mary Lovely, a senior fellow at the Peterson Institute for International Economics.</p><p> “The question is, &#39;What can they do that is going to be effective?&#39; ” she added. “Everywhere they turn, they&#39;ll find constraints.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=369E869E-DD3C-46A0-B12E-D92EC6AD14BE&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchinas-fading-recovery-tests-policy-makers-economic-playbook-8ce334f9&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> China has been the most populous nation in the world since at least 1750. But in April, India&#39;s population is set to surpass China&#39;s. WSJ examines what this shift in population could mean for the future of each country, as well as the global economy. Photo illustration: Jacob Anderson Nelson/WSJ<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Despite mounting evidence of a weakening recovery, Chinese officials have so far avoided large-scale stimulus, focusing instead on trimming key interest rates and easing curbs in the property market, such as making more households eligible to buy homes in a number of cities.</p><p> “It is unsurprising that policy makers are becoming increasingly concerned and have made some effort to shore up the economy. But measures so far have fallen short of what is needed to provide a meaningful boost to the economy,” economists at Capital Economics wrote in a note to clients, while cutting their forecast for full-year growth to 5.5%, from 6% previously.</p><p> The Wall Street Journal reported in June that <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-cuts-rates-to-prop-up-flagging-recovery-6fe3ec72?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Beijing was considering issuing roughly one trillion yuan</a> , equivalent to about $140 billion, of bonds to help indebted local governments and boost business confidence. The special bonds would be used to finance infrastructure projects and other initiatives aimed at boosting economic growth, or used to help local governments repay their debt.</p><p> Top officials are due to meet this month and are expected to announce another bundle of measures. Many economists expect them to be limited in scope.</p><p></p> Rory Green, head of Asia and China research at TS Lombard in London, said he expects officials to take steps to ease funding strains at local governments to free up financing for infrastructure investment. Steps could include issuing more bonds or prodding banks to extend new loans.<p></p><p> He said he also expects the government to announce small measures to lift consumption, such as handing out vouchers that need to be spent. But Green doesn&#39;t think such meager support will be sufficient for most consumers.</p><p> More economists, and even some former officials, have begun calling for Beijing to adopt a new approach to stimulate growth—one aimed at <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/deflation-looms-in-china-as-rebound-continues-to-lose-steam-b0d66d7e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">shoring up consumer spending</a> .</p><p> Last month, Mao Zhenhua, co-director of Renmin University&#39;s Institute for Economic Research, called on officials to provide direct subsidies for Chinese households to boost consumption. Zhang Jun, a professor at Fudan University, pointed out that China needs to raise household incomes to boost domestic demand instead of plowing more money into infrastructure investments.</p><p> “Well-targeted fiscal stimulus could be helpful in boosting household consumption in the short run as well as growth rebalancing in the longer term,” said Eswar Prasad, professor of trade and economics at Cornell University and a former head of the International Monetary Fund&#39;s China division.</p><p> Policies aimed at boosting consumption, he said, would serve the short-term objective of getting the economy revved up again, as well help meet the longer-term goal of rebalancing the economy away from an overreliance on investment and exports.</p><p> Other steps could include measures to make it easier for Chinese workers to move around to find jobs and more spending in areas such as healthcare, pensions and unemployment insurance.</p><p> But those shifts are unlikely to materialize soon, since such moves will require sweeping changes to the fabric of society that could have a destabilizing effect on tens of millions of people&#39;s lives.</p><p> During past rounds of downturns, including the 2008-09 global financial crisis, Chinese authorities unleashed hundreds of billions of dollars to fuel a multiyear construction boom and stave off a sharp economic slowdown.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>What is your outlook for China&#39;s economy?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> But the rapid buildup in debt and inflated asset prices that such an approach created, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-property-market-enters-troubling-new-phase-1fe3143d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">especially in the housing market</a> , created its own problems—and prompted Chinese leader Xi Jinping to champion a deleveraging campaign starting in 2016 that continues to this day.</p><p> “To go back to that aspect of the playbook really goes against the grain of what they try to achieve now,” said Stephen Roach, a senior fellow at Yale University.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GS" class="company-name">Goldman Sachs</a> economists expect that any property and infrastructure stimulus is likely to be “targeted and moderate,” thanks to already-elevated debt levels and Beijing&#39;s desire to avoid reinflating a housing bubble that it spent so many years struggling to tamp down.</p><p> At the same time, authorities have continued to pledge more help for businesses and manufacturers in the form of tax cuts, rather than offering subsidies for households directly—a policy choice that analysts say has only encouraged ordinary Chinese to sock away more for a rainy day instead of spending.</p><p> Others believe that with the country&#39;s economy still largely on track to reach the roughly 5% growth target for the year, authorities will be in no rush to step up stimulus measures in the near term.</p><p> “The real threat is what happens to China&#39;s economy in 2024 and onwards,” said Shehzad Qazi, managing director of China Beige Book, a research firm. “A lot of the dry powder is certainly going to be saved in the coming year.”</p><p> Write to Stella Yifan Xie at <a href="mailto:stella.xie@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">stella.xie@wsj.com</a> and Jason Douglas at <a href="mailto:jason.douglas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jason.douglas@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 12:06:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-fading-recovery-tests-policy-makers-economic-playbook-8ce334f9</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-fading-recovery-tests-policy-makers-economic-playbook-8ce334f9<author><![CDATA[Stella Yifan XieJason Douglas]]></author><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Respiratory Tract Diseases</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>Outbreaks/Epidemics</category><category> Novel Coronaviruses</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>recession</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>respiratory tract diseases</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>outbreaks</category><category> epidemics</category><category> novel coronaviruses</category><category>传染性疾病</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Divorce Parties Are a New Hot Invite. ‘It Sort of Ended Up as a Really Fun Funeral.’]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>随着社会广泛接受破裂的婚姻，许多刚刚离婚的人更有勇气对自己进行抨击。 &#39;错误结束&#39; <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-814552?width=1000&amp;height=562" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>视频：瓦夏·科洛图沙<span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001042895"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001042895"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/lane-florsheim" itemprop="url" rel="author">莱恩·弗洛舍姆</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 17 日上午 7:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/divorce-parties-registries-marriage-1ed745b9"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web
          bigtophero
"></div><p>布兰迪·斯特勒斯 (Brandi Stellers) 离婚后，她邀请密友参加五月的一场晚会。她调制了招牌鸡尾酒，挂上了“再见费利西亚”的横幅，并分发假玫瑰花瓣并抛向空中。</p><p>派对装饰品包括一张从中间撕下来的一对企鹅的照片。</p><p> “我把企鹅撕成两半，因为企鹅是一夫一妻制的鸟类，应该终身交配，”她说。 “好吧，我不再是你的企鹅了。”</p><p>新近离婚的人正在为自己举办井喷式的狂欢，以纪念他们从不幸的婚姻中解放出来，就像反向单身派对一样。在俄亥俄州哥伦布市一家云计算公司工作的斯特勒斯说：“我想庆祝的不是离婚，而是一个新的篇章，与那些我爱的人一起庆祝，他们都希望我过得最好。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="803" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817952?width=639&amp;height=803" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">布兰迪·斯特勒斯在她的离婚后晚会上。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：布兰迪·斯特勒斯</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>在历史的大部分时间里，离婚并不是一件被全世界吹捧的事件。现在，文化转变正在进行。美国的离婚率一直在下降，但那些离婚的人却可以更自由地宣扬自己的分手。盖洛普民意调查显示，认为离婚在道德上可以接受的美国成年人数量已创历史新高。</p><p> “由于社会压力和刻板印象，离婚曾经是一件令人羞耻的事情，”离婚律师妮可·索多玛（Nicole Sodoma）说，她就这个话题写了《请不要说对不起》一书。 “但今天，人们真的决定消除这种社会耻辱，转而接受离婚作为我们中的一些人经历的人生的另一个阶段。”</p><p>在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/ETSY" class="company-name">Etsy</a>和亚马逊上，品牌出售 splitsville 的周边商品，包括“End of an Error”腰带、“Thank U Next”玫瑰金箔气球和“I do.我做到了。我完成了”T 恤。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PINS" class="">Pinterest</a>数据洞察全球总监 Swasti Sarna 表示<span class="company-name-type">，</span>在分享创意的在线平台 Pinterest 上，“搜索趋势表明人们正在以新的视角看待离婚”。</p><p> 2022 年 6 月，Pinterest 上“离婚派对游戏”的搜索量同比增长 80%，“离婚蛋糕”的搜索量同比增长 50%。 Pinterest 的数据显示，离婚派对装饰创意（35%）和“离婚礼物”（30%）的搜索量也出现了激增。</p><p> “这只是一种感觉，我并不为此感到羞耻，”曼哈顿和布鲁克林的房地产经纪人纳丁·亚当森 (Nadine Adamson) 说，她举办了一场离婚派对。 “我认为在纽约结婚超过 10 年——我结婚 12 年——是一个巨大的成功。”</p><p>亚当森让朋友从洛杉矶飞往纽约，他们预订了她结婚时住过的酒店套房。 “在同一家酒店欣赏同样的景色，感觉就像以一种非常美妙的方式结束了，”她说。</p><p>他们四人在套房里烧鼠尾草，以消除负面情绪，在房间里放满气球，出去吃饭，然后过夜。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="696" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817050?width=700&amp;height=696" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">纳丁·亚当森 (Nadine Adamson) 在她的离婚派对上，在她参加婚礼的酒店房间里。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：克里斯塔·蕾妮</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>亚当森还继续在 Instagram 上发布话题标签#divorceparty，并不是因为她一直扔它们，而是为了突出她的新生活，比如用舒适的燃木壁炉升级她的上流社会。</p><p> “我猜离婚派对是一回事？”几个月前，一位 Reddit 用户发表了一篇帖子，吸引了近 4,000 条评论。海报上有一张来自一对正在举办联合派对的离婚夫妇的邀请函的照片。 “另外也欢迎——我们的也会在那里！”它说。</p><p>加拿大艾伯塔省的心理健康辅导员克里斯·马克斯 (Kris Marks) 表示，当一位朋友邀请他庆祝离婚时，他最初感到很矛盾。马克斯也是前夫的朋友，他认为他不知道这个派对。</p><p> “我有很多想法，比如，我们应该庆祝承诺的结束吗？”马克斯说。 “我反复思考，得出的结论是，是的，婚姻制度就是这样，但如果你选择摆脱它，那是一件很难的事情，应该庆祝一个新的开始。我完全赞成它。”</p><p>他的结婚 12 年的朋友举办了一顿聚餐，然后一行人出去镇上过夜。 “这是我和另一个男人，也许还有 10 个女人，就像是单身派对上墙上的一只苍蝇，”他说。马克斯给他的朋友买了一个月的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/dating-apps-paid-memberships-tinder-raya-hinge-11664984612?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Bumble Premium</a>作为礼物。</p><p>一些企业迎合新近离婚的男性。例如，Stripe Street Studio 是一家成立于 2020 年的设计公司，专门帮助离婚和单身男性建立住房。该公司表示，在 Pinterest 上，现在流行的流行语“离婚爸爸审美”的搜索量 6 月份比去年同期增长了近 300%。</p><p>不过，有传闻称，举行彻底离婚游行的女性多于男性。</p><p> “作为一个男人，我们不称之为离婚派对，我们称之为‘我们去喝酒吧，’马克斯解释道。 “我们只是以不同的方式应对。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817046?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">妮可·索多玛 (Nicole Sodoma) 离婚后，买了一辆老式汽车，以 1998 年浪漫喜剧《斯特拉如何找回她的魅力》的名字命名为斯特拉 (Stella)。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Darius Evans/DME Imagery</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>现在，人们可以找到帮助离婚者补充物资的登记网站，因为只有一半的夫妇得到了意大利面机、香料架或 Le Creuset 炊具。</p><p>奥利维亚·德莱森·豪厄尔 (Olivia Dreizen Howell) 于 2019 年分居后，一直住在婚姻住所，但婚姻住所突然变得空荡荡的。 “我的一半东西都不见了，”她说，其他物品都是她婚礼登记处的充满情感的物品。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817051?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">奥利维亚·德莱森·豪厄尔签署离婚文件。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Fresh Starts 登记处</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>因此，她和姐姐 Jenny Dreizen 在 2021 年为有同样经历的人们创立了 Fresh Starts 网站。</p><p>该公司帮助新婚夫妇建立礼物登记处，为新家的特定房间补充库存。最受欢迎的登记项目是厨房和浴室。他们还提供专家网络，例如房地产经纪人、宽恕教练和帮助策划离婚派对的离婚导乐。</p><p> 《艾米丽·波斯特礼仪：百年纪念版》一书的合著者莉齐·波斯特表示，艾米丽·波斯特研究所目前并不认为离婚当事人或离婚后登记是合适的。</p><p>她说：“离婚后与朋友们聚在一起，找到一种方法来结束这一章，感觉良好，这是一件非常令人支持的事情。” “我认为称其为离婚派对感觉有点不切实际。”</p><p>纽约的法律助理艾莉森·麦克怀特 (Allison McWhite) 表示，筹划自己的离婚派对给她带来了一种掌控感。 “很长一段时间以来，似乎有什么事情发生在我身上，向我冲来，而不是我去处理它，”她说。</p><p>她在朋友的公寓里举行了庆祝活动，音乐录影带被投影到墙上，黑色气球散落在地板上，烛台上的蜡滴在装有烛台的空酒瓶上。一个白色蛋糕上涂着樱桃红色的糖霜，上面写着“刚刚离婚”。麦克怀特 (McWhite) 身穿黑色蕾丝透明连衣裙，涂着红色口红，身穿毛皮大衣，符合<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/forget-wedding-dresses-divorce-style-has-arrived-11612616414?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">20 世纪 50 年代离婚时尚</a>派对着装要求。 （想想玛丽莲·梦露 1954 年与乔·迪马吉奥离婚时的情景，当时她穿着小黑裙、脚踩高跟鞋、戴着白手套去法院。） </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/9c101278-b1d5-4ed6-915b-14735a357de8.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>客人们跳舞到凌晨，庆祝她新生活的开始。</p><p> “这最终成为一场非常有趣的葬礼，”麦克怀特说。</p><p>对于一些离婚者来说，试图庆祝可能会适得其反，让人感觉像是在提醒他们失去亲人。</p><p> “当你离婚时，你就失去了一半的朋友，”伦敦的离婚律师阿伊莎·瓦尔达格 (Ayesha Vardag) 说，她的朋友鼓励她在离婚后举办派对。在他们的坚持下，她在一家酒吧楼上预订了一间不错的房间，她说那里有吵闹的音乐和“一些舞蹈，但还不够，因为人确实不够多。”</p><p> “为了好玩，压力很大，”她说。 “后来，我觉得我应该让自己感到非常沮丧，然后慢慢走出困境。”</p><p>旅游博主玛雅·普罗斯霍尔特 (Maja Proescholdt) 表示，她的离婚程序在没有律师的情况下完成，时间足够长，当文书工作完成时，她的大部分悲伤已经平复，她已经准备好参加派对了。</p><p>她的姐姐提供了一顶王冠和一条“最终离婚”的腰带。乐队出去跳舞，俱乐部的 DJ 喊道：“让我们为 Maja 的离婚派对举办吧！”</p><p> “那对我来说是人生的巅峰时刻，”她说。</p><p>写信给 Lane Florsheim： <a href="mailto:lane.florsheim@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">lane.florsheim@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/7014063b-a894-4b50-b6a3-a3b3e88591aa.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/divorce-parties-registries-marriage-1ed745b9</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/divorce-parties-registries-marriage-1ed745b9<author><![CDATA[Lane Florsheim]]></author><category>阿赫德</category><category>世界时尚</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>结婚/离婚</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>婚姻</category><category>离婚</category></item></channel></rss>